dialogueText.dialogue:
 Yes, I say you are the beautifull'st of Women;
and that my Lord in your enjoyment is the
happiest --

 You might safer
Ha' sent it so, and your own right hand with it;
Then to have drawn my just revenge upon you.

 In your Aunts presence, and your Unkles house;
Though I were not his friend; could you be so
outragious? I muse I see him here though.

 I hope his impudent Wife has not told him all; 
if shee has, where's his remedy in this Womans
Lawcase?
